The genome with identifier 511145.12 has 4639675 base pairs and name Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655. It is considered a Reference genome by NCBI. The genome has 1 contigs, 4549 known protein-coding regions, and is considered Good quality. It has a taxonomic classification identifier of 511145, a species of Escherichia coli, a genus of Escherichia, belongs to the Enterobacteriaceae taxonomic family, belongs to the Gammaproteobacteria taxonomic class, is a member of the Enterobacterales order, is a member of the Proteobacteria phylum, and is part of the Bacteria domain.
